model_explanation: the prosodic focus in S1 is on "SUE," meaning Sam gave apples only to Sue and no one else. S2 says Sam also gave apples to Rob, which contradicts the idea that Sue was the only recipient of apples.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave apples only to Bill. S2 states that Sam didn’t give Mary apples, which is independent. It does not confirm or contradict the claim that Bill is the only one Sam gave apples to—S2 simply speaks about Mary.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "MARY," meaning Sam gave oranges only to Mary and no one else. S2 says Sam also gave Ellen oranges, which contradicts the first sentence’s restriction.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "APPLES," meaning Sam gave Ellen only apples (not other fruits). S2 says Sam didn’t give Tom apples, which is independent from S1. It does not confirm or contradict the focus on the kind of thing given to Ellen.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ROB," meaning Sam gave bananas only to Rob and no one else. S2 says Sam also gave Rob oranges, which contradicts the idea that bananas were all that Rob got.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave bananas only to Bill and no one else. S2 states that Sam didn’t give Bill grapes, and this is entailed. It aligns with the fact that Bill only got bananas, not anything else.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ELLEN," meaning Sam gave oranges only to Ellen and no one else. S2 says Sam didn’t give Ellen grapes, which is entailed, as it supports that Ellen only received oranges.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "MARY," meaning Sam gave bananas only to Mary. S2 says Sam didn’t give Ellen bananas, which is independent. It doesn’t affect or contradict the fact that only Mary got bananas.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave bananas only to Bill. S2 says Sam didn’t give Tom bananas, which is entailed, as bananas were only for Bill.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "SUE," meaning Sam gave oranges only to Sue and no one else. S2 says Sam didn’t give Sue grapes, which is entailed by S1. Sue received only oranges, not grapes.
